The paper proposes a methodology for discovering solutions to a functional design problem using a combination of machine learning and evolutionary algorithms. This involves learning an effective search space through a variational autoencoder (VAE), building a surrogate model for functional designs, and using a genetic algorithm to optimize the designs. The paper also uses a car-launcher mechanism as a test domain to evaluate the methodology. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics), as the paper involves machine learning and optimization techniques for functional design. The other likely sub-categories are cs.CE (Computational Engineering), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as the paper involves learning effective search spaces and building surrogate models, which are common topics in these sub-categories.
